Package io.github.luccaflower.result

Interface Result<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The object-type contained within the Ok-variant
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ForwardingResult<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Err, Ok
    public interface Result<T>

    Result is a type that represents either the success or failure of a given operation, similar to the Either and Result types seen in Scala.

    The interface provides a few abstract methods along with a number of default methods implemented with respect to these methods.

    Furthermore, the ForwardingResult interface is provided for easy implementation of wrapper-classes around Result-types.

    Author:
    Lucca Kaasgaard Christiansen

      • ifOk

        default Result<T> ifOk​(Consumer<? super T> onOk)
        Passes the object contained within an Ok-variant to the passed function. Assuming the consumer has no side effects that mutate the Result, this is a noop, that leaves the Result unaffected. This method does nothing on Error-variants.

      • ifErr

        default Result<T> ifErr​(Consumer<? super Exception> onErr)
        Passes the object contained within an Error-variant to the passed function. Assuming the consumer has no side effects that mutate the Result, this is a noop, that leaves the Result unaffected. This method does nothing on Ok-variants.

      • andCollector

        static <T> Collector<Result<T>,​List<Result<T>>,​Result<List<T>>> andCollector()
        Converts a List<Result<T> to a Result<List<T>>. If any Result contained within the List is an Error, it returns the first Error

      • orCollector

        static <T> Collector<Result<T>,​List<Result<T>>,​Result<List<T>>> orCollector()
        Converts a List<Result<T> to a Result<List<T>>. If any Results within the List are Ok, then it returns an Ok containing all objects contained within Ok-variants. Otherwise, it returns the last encountered Error.
